edu.washington.cs.cse490h.lib
Class MessageLayer

java.lang.Object
  edu.washington.cs.cse490h.lib.MessageLayer

public class MessageLayer
extends java.lang.Object

 
 Class with main method that starts up a Manager. Either an Emulator or a Simulator

 Usage: java MessageLayer [options]
 General Options:
  -h --help=                               - Print usage message [default false]
  -v --version=                            - Print program version [default false]

 Execution Options:
  -s --simulate=                           - Simulate [default false]
  -e --emulate=                            - Emulate [default false]
  -n --nodeClass=                           - Node class to use [default ]
  --routerHostname=                         - Router hostname [default localhost]
  --routerPort=                                - Router port [default -1]
  -t --timestep=                              - Time step, in ms [default 1000]
  -r --seed=                                  - Random seed
  -c --commandFile=                         - Command file [default ]
  -f --failureLvlInt=                          - Failure level, a number between 0 and 4 [default 4]

 Debugging Options:
  -L --synopticTotallyOrderedLogFilename=   - Synoptic totally ordered log filename [default ]
  -l --synopticPartiallyOrderedLogFilename= - Synoptic partially ordered log filename [default ]
  -o --replayOutputFilename=                - Replay output filename [default ]
  --replayInputFilename=                    - Replay input filename [default ]
